    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>*In nomine sancte et individue trinitatis. Anno dominice incarnationis
                        millesimo centesimo quartodecimo, <persName key="#childOf #Witness"
                            ref="#people/125">Matildis</persName> dei gratia si quid est.*
                        Venerabilibus locis in quibus qui pro Christo pauperes facti sunt divinis
                        misteriis deserviunt merito debemus opere consolationis porrigere, et eorum
                        necessitatibus pietatis intuitu subvenire; et licet omnibus ecclesiis
                        debitores simus, illis tamen propensius debemus exhibere hcaritatis affectum
                        que in nostris possessionibus constitute et pro parentes nostros constructe
                        sunt Qua propter cum ego Matildis <rs key="#childOf">filia</rs> quondam
                            <persName key="#Marquis/duke" ref="#people/1">Bonefacii</persName>
                        <rs key="#Marquis/duke #parentOf">marchionis</rs> cum quibusdam nostris
                        fidelibus apud <placeName ref="#places/2400"><orgName
                                key="#Monasteries #Abbots #Monasteries #Curtes #Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters #Forests #Pigs"
                                ref="#juridical_persons/2001">Sanctum
                            Benedictum</orgName></placeName> veniremus et donnum <rs key="#Abbots"
                            >abbatem</rs>
                        <persName key="#Abbots" ref="#people/2189">Albericum</persName> in
                        infirmitate sua visitassemus, illam sanctam congregationem vidimus et super
                        mortificatione eorum compacientes, compunctione misericordiae, devotione
                        hcaritatis, ad eorum sustentationem quedam transferre ex nostra largitate
                        curavimus. Itaque coram ilio venerabili collegio super sanctum <rs
                            key="#Altars">altare</rs> beati Benedicti investituram posuimus,
                        condonantes <rs key="#Albergaria/gifori">albergariam</rs> et quicquid nobis
                        quolibet modo pertinere videbatur in cunctis possessionibus <rs
                            key="#Monasteries">monasterii</rs>, videlicet in <placeName
                            ref="#places/2400">Sancto Benedicto iuxta Largionem</placeName> et in
                            <placeName ref="#places/482">Burbaxio</placeName>, in
                            <placeName>Casale</placeName>, <placeName ref="#places/2476"
                            >Septingenti</placeName>, <placeName ref="#places/2417"
                            >Clustello</placeName>, <placeName ref="#places/2930"
                            >Gabiana</placeName>, <placeName ref="#places/2900"
                            >Marzaneta</placeName>, <placeName ref="#places/2929">Capite
                            Vici</placeName>, <geogName ref="#estates/80"><rs key="#Curtes"
                                >curte</rs>
                            <placeName ref="#places/362">Villola</placeName></geogName>,
                            <placeName>Vale de Orti</placeName> , <placeName ref="#places/2414"
                            >Gunzaga</placeName> et in omnibus aliis, non solum in his que iam ad
                        ecclesiam pervenerunt, sed etiam que in posterum quocumque modo pervenire
                        videbuntur. Et quicquid nobis causa albergariae vel aliqua occasione
                        alicuius rei actenus pertinere videbatur, hoc totum ad dominium monasterii
                        transeat, cum tanta libertate ut neque nos neque successores nostri neque
                        aliqua persona sub nostra occasione in possessionibus prefati cenobii aliquo
                        ius secundum quod dictum est audeat ulterius vendicare vel causare, pro
                        mercede et remedio animae nostrae et parentum nostrorum. Addimus preter ea
                        nostrae liberalitati ut <rs key="#Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters"
                            >licenciam habeant rectores monasterii in omnibus <rs key="#Forests"
                                >silvis</rs> nostris ubicumque eas habemus et in quibus <rs
                                key="#Pigs">porci</rs> nostri et nostrorum hominum mittentur porcos
                            suos et suorum hominurn mittere et <rs key="#Public_exactions"
                                >escaticum</rs> totum de suis porcis et suorum hominum habere</rs>,
                        quod parentes nostros in quibusdam supradictis silvis testimonio plurimorum
                        hominum predicto monasterio concessisse cognovimus. Volumus etiam et
                        firmiter precipimus ut homines monasterii ad aidam que ad <rs key="#Animals"
                            >bestias</rs> capiendas in forestis fieri solebat ulterius non
                        compellantur, aut etiam vocentur ut eam faciant; nec liceat nobis ullo
                        tempore nolle quod voluimus, sed quod semel a nobis factum est inviolabile
                        in perpetuum consistat. Quod si nos vel nostri successores aut nostri <rs
                            key="#Missus">missi</rs> sive ulla persona hec que superius compreensa
                        sunt infringere aliquo ingenio temptaverit, <rs key="#Penalty">centum libras
                            denariorum lucensium</rs> componat, medietatem monasterio et medietatem
                            <rs key="#Camera">parti publicae</rs>, hoc tamen scripto in suo robore
                        permanente. Quod ut verius credatur et firmius ab omnibus teneatur nostrae
                        propriae manus inscriptione firmavimus. + Factum est hoc die octava mensis
                        novembris indictione septima. + <rs key="#Witness">Testes</rs> interfuerunt
                            <rs key="#Count">comes</rs>
                        <persName key="#Witness #Count" ref="#people/2197">Albertus</persName>,
                            <persName key="#Witness" ref="#people/3500">Ardoinus</persName> de
                        Palude, <persName key="#Witness #childOf" ref="#people/2199">Ugo</persName>
                        et <persName key="#Witness #childOf" ref="#people/3511">Albertus</persName>
                        filii <persName ref="#people/3510">Manfredi</persName>, <persName
                            key="#Witness" ref="#people/3526">Araldus</persName> de Melegnato,
                            <persName key="#Witness #childOf"><name ref="Gherardus/f. Bosonis"
                                >Gerardo</name></persName> filius Bosonis, <persName key="#Witness"
                                ><name ref="Hugo/de Baiso">Ugo</name></persName> de Baise, <persName
                            key="#Witness" ref="#people/2193">Saxo</persName> de Bibianello,
                            <persName key="#Agricultural_workers #Witness"><name
                                ref="Rodelandus/massarius">Rolandus</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Agricultural_workers">massarius</rs>, <persName key="#Witness"
                            ref="#people/3517">Opizo</persName>, <persName key="#Witness"><name
                                ref="Rainerius">Raginerius</name></persName>, <persName
                            key="#Witness" ref="#people/3528">Vuibertus</persName> de Gunzaga,
                            <persName key="#Witness"><name ref="Hugo">Ugo</name></persName>
                        et <persName key="#Witness"><name ref="Hludouuicus/de Gubernolo"
                                >Lodoicus</name></persName> de Gubernulo , <persName key="#Witness"
                                ><name ref="Maragone">Maragnolus</name></persName> et <persName
                            key="#Witness"><name ref="Petrus/de Opizo/de Burbassio"
                            >Petrus</name></persName> de Opizo de Burbassio, <persName
                            key="#Witness"><name ref="Iohannes/de Frixa">Iohannes</name></persName>
                        de Frixa. + Ego <persName key="#Judge #Writer" ref="#people/2185"
                            >Ubaldus</persName>
                        <rs key="#Judge">iudex</rs> hoc <rs key="#Writer">scripsi</rs>, compievi et
                        dedi. Ego <persName key="#Causidicus #Witness" ref="#people/3530"
                            >Odaldus</persName>
                        <rs key="#Causidicus">cauridicus</rs> interfui et subscripsi. Matilda Dei
                        gratia si quid est buscripsi. (S.) Ego <persName key="#Notary #Witness"
                                ><name ref="Iohannes/notarius">Iohannes</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Notary">notarius</rs> Sacri Palacii his interfui et scripsi. </ab>
                </div>
            </div>
